 {"id":"bd-55qb","title":"Add ThrottleInjector unit tests for comprehensive coverage","description":"The ThrottleInjector in ffs-block has zero unit tests despite having complex features: base latency, bandwidth throttling, probabilistic stalls, Cx deadline integration, runtime config updates, and deterministic RNG. Add comprehensive unit tests covering: (1) basic latency injection, (2) bandwidth calculation, (3) deterministic stall triggering, (4) runtime config update, (5) reset behavior, (6) log accumulation and sequencing.","notes":"ThrottleInjector already has 12+ unit tests covering passthrough, latency, bandwidth, stalls, progressive degradation, reset, concurrency, debug format, and determinism. No gap to fill.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-02-27T22:52:09.407530558Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-27T22:52:38.762372211Z","closed_at":"2026-02-27T22:52:38.762295397Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
